  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Ketamine and opioid are known to improve the intubating condition, respectively. Combination
      of ketamine and opioid potentiate analgesic effect and give hemodynamic stability in
      complementary manner. Therefore, the combination use of ketamine and remifentanil could be
      useful for acceptable intubating condition in the general anesthesia without the use of
      neuromuscular blocking agent. Generally, induction dose of ketamine ranges between 1 and 2
      mg. There was no report about the optimal dose of remifentanil with 1 or 2 mg ketamine
      induction dose for intubation without neuromuscular blocking agent. The investigators focus
      on remifentanil dose using Dixon's up and down method.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
