  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>acceptability of intubation condition</measure>
    <time_frame>during and after intubation, about 2 minute</time_frame>
    <description>For assessment of intubation condition, 5 variables will be individually evaluated though 3 point scale (excellent, good, poor). If all variables are graded as excellent, intubation condition will be excellent. If at least 1 variable is poor, it will be reported as poor. Otherwise, it will be reported as good. Good and excellent will be considered to be acceptable intubating condition. Poor will be reported as unacceptable intubating condition.
Laryngoscope easiness
Vocal cord position
Vocal cord movement
Movement of limb
Coughing</description>
  </primary_outcome>
